div.p: The requirements for capabilities of a server implementing Australian Digital Health Agency FHIR RESTful Endpoints (au.digitalhealth.r4).

ol.li: Support the ADHA Core Patient resource profile.
Implement the RESTful behavior according to the FHIR specification.
Follow the requirements documented in the Policy page.

Return the following response classes:
(Status 400): invalid parameter
(Status 401/4xx): unauthorized request
(Status 403): insufficient scopes
(Status 404): unknown resource
Support JSON source formats for all ADHA interactions.
Declare a CapabilityStatement identifying the list of profiles, operations, and search parameters supported.
Follow the guidance documented in the Guidance page
Support XML source formats for all ADHA interactions.
Identify the ADHA profiles supported as part of the FHIR meta.profile attribute for each instance.

b.title: GET past versions of resources (vread interaction)
GET all set of resources of the type (search interaction)
PUT a new resource version (update interaction)
PATCH a new resource version (patch interaction)
GET changes to a resource (history interaction on instance)
GET changes for all resources of the type (history interaction on type)
